Coal Mining Inspection Reclamation activities are as closely monitored as coal removal activities to ensure that required performance standards are met and the reclamation plans approved in the companies' mining permits are followed.
Coal mine inspections are performed monthly.
On-site inspections serve three primary functions: 1.
Ensure an operation is functioning in a manner consistent with applicable state laws; 2.
Ensure an operation is fully complying with the conditions of the permit; and
